                    <h1 class="about-title page-title small-frc">About Me</h1>
                    <div class="my-professional-title heading small-frc">My Experience</div>
                    <div class="my-professional-desc desc">
                        Senior Software Engineer with 3+ years at Walmart building high-throughput, distributed backend systems for large-scale
                        supply chain operations. I work across Java/Spring Boot microservices, Apache Kafka event-driven systems, Kubernetes,
                        and Microsoft Azure, with a focus on reliability, scale, and cost efficiency.
                    </div>
                    <div class="my-professional-desc desc">
                        <div class="my-professional-job-name">
                            Senior Software Engineer at Walmart, Inc. - Jun 2025 to Present
                        </div>
                        <div class="my-professional-job-desc">
                            Leading modernization of a 20-year legacy warehouse management monolith into cloud-native microservices deployed across
                            11 Sam's Club Fulfillment Centers. I own end-to-end inbound backend systems and helped architect one-click disaster
                            recovery with automatic SQL and Kafka failover, reducing recovery time from hours to minutes during regional outages.
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="my-professional-desc desc">
                        <div class="my-professional-job-name">
                            Software Engineer III at Walmart, Inc. - Jul 2022 to Jun 2025
                        </div>
                        <div class="my-professional-job-desc">
                            Built event-driven inbound order processing pipelines (Kafka, IBM MQ) supporting 20,000+ orders at peak scale,
                            eliminated release-day outages through zero-downtime migration strategies, reduced Azure cloud spend by $80,000+/month,
                            and improved operational stability with self-healing APIs and CI/CD automation.
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="my-professional-desc desc">
                        <div class="my-professional-job-name">
                            Teaching Assistant at University of Dayton - Mar 2021 to May 2022
                        </div>
                        <div class="my-professional-job-desc">
                            Supported a graduate Algorithms Design course across 3 semesters (350+ students), contributing to assignment and exam
                            design while providing detailed feedback on algorithmic complexity analysis.
                        </div>
                    </div>
